<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,289,388]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,289,315]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[281,544,290,316]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spatulatus">
<emphasis box="[281,544,290,316]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Cyrtocapsus spatulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[561,643,290,317]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–57" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1907,1931]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-32@38.[170,1418,181,1883]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 49–57. Habitus images of Cyrtocapsus spp. 49–51, C. rostratus. 49, male dorsal aspect. 50, female lectotype, dorsal aspect. 51, female lectotype, lateral aspect. 52–54, C. schaffneri. 52, male, dorsal aspect. 53, female, dorsal aspect. 54, C. female, lateral aspect. 55, C. spatulatus, holotype male, dorsal aspect. 56, 57. C. suturalis. 56, male, dorsal aspect. 57, male, lateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646379" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646379/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
) is recognized by the overall black body, the pale antennal segment I, with the apical third to half fuscous, the largely fuscous antennal segment II, with only the base pale; the uniformly yellowish-white legs, including the coxae; and the broadly rounded right paramere (
<figureCitation box="[1091,1175,362,388]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–98" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,489,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-179@41.[182,1405,489,1830]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 85–98. Male genitalia of Cyrtocapsus spp. 85, 86, C. mesoamericanus. 85, left paramere. 86, right paramere. 87, 88, C. metafemoratus. 87, left paramere. 88, right paramere. 89, 90, C. pallipes. 89, left paramere. 90, right paramere. 91, 92, C. paraguaiensis. 91 left paramere. 92, right paramere. 93, 94, C. rostratus. 93, left paramere. 94, right paramere. 95, 96, C. schaffneri. 95, left paramere. 96 right paramere. 97, 98, C. spatulatus. 97, left paramere. 98, right paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646387/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 98</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646385" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6646385" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646385/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" startId="40.[151,232,1886,1910]" targetBox="[170,1418,412,1861]" targetPageId="40">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,1886,2018]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,314,1886,1910]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Figures 71– 84.</emphasis>
Male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[497,671,1886,1909]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[497,624,1886,1909]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Cyrtocapsus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
71, 72, 
<taxonomicName box="[751,836,1886,1910]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cyrtocapus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fiuzai">
<emphasis box="[751,836,1886,1910]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">C. fiuzai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 71, left paramere. 72, right paramere. 73, 74, 
<taxonomicName box="[1304,1430,1886,1910]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabratus">
<emphasis box="[1304,1430,1886,1910]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">C. glabratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 73, left paramere. 74, right paramere. 75, 76, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carvalho" authorityYear="1954" box="[608,759,1922,1946]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grenadensis">
<emphasis box="[608,759,1922,1946]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">C. grenadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 75, left paramere. 76, right paramere. 77–79, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carvalho" authorityYear="1954" box="[1229,1352,1922,1946]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haitianus">
<emphasis box="[1229,1352,1922,1946]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">C. haitianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 77, left paramere. 78, endosoma. 79, right paramere. 80, 81, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1909" box="[683,832,1958,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[683,832,1958,1982]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">C. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 80, left paramere. 81, right paramere. 82–84, 
<taxonomicName box="[1301,1392,1958,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lazelli">
<emphasis box="[1301,1392,1958,1982]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">C. lazelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 82, left paramere. 83, endosoma. 84, right paramere.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,151,465]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
It is similar to several other black species, with pale legs, such as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergroth" authorityYear="1910" box="[919,1038,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Miccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elutipes">
<emphasis box="[919,1038,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. elutipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1052,1185,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–28" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[176,1412,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-32@14.[176,1412,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 18–28. Habitus images of Cyrtocapsus spp. 18, 19, C. discalis, holotype male. 18, dorsal aspect. 19, lateral aspect. 20–22, C. elutipes. 20, male, dorsal aspect. 21, female, dorsal aspect. 22, female, lateral aspect. 23, 24, C. femoralis, lectotype male. 23, dorsal aspect. 24, lateral aspect. 25, 26, C. fiuzai. 25, male, dorsal aspect. 26, female, dorsal aspect. 27, 28, C. glabratus, holotype male. 27, dorsal aspect. 28, lateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646371" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646371/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Figs. 20–22</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1884" box="[1246,1366,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Pirithous" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallipes">
<emphasis box="[1246,1366,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. pallipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 40–48" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1907,1931]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-16@31.[170,1418,181,1883]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 40–48. Habitus images of Cyrtocapsus spp. 40, 41, C. metafemoratus. 40, male, dorsal aspect. 41, holotype female, dorsal aspect. 42, 43, C. nordestinus. 42, male, dorsal aspect. 43, male, lateral aspect. 44, 45, C. pallipes. 44, male, dorsal aspect. 45, female, dorsal aspect. 46, 47, C. paraensis, holotype female (of C. bolivianus). 46, dorsal aspect. 47, lateral aspect. 48, C. paraguaiensis, holotype female, dorsal aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646375" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646375/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Figs. 44, 45</figureCitation>
) but differs from the former by the color of antennae and the large spatulate right paramere and from the latter by the color of the antennae, the white middle and hind coxae (versus brown), and the right paramere (
<figureCitation box="[1299,1384,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–98" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,489,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-179@41.[182,1405,489,1830]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 85–98. Male genitalia of Cyrtocapsus spp. 85, 86, C. mesoamericanus. 85, left paramere. 86, right paramere. 87, 88, C. metafemoratus. 87, left paramere. 88, right paramere. 89, 90, C. pallipes. 89, left paramere. 90, right paramere. 91, 92, C. paraguaiensis. 91 left paramere. 92, right paramere. 93, 94, C. rostratus. 93, left paramere. 94, right paramere. 95, 96, C. schaffneri. 95, left paramere. 96 right paramere. 97, 98, C. spatulatus. 97, left paramere. 98, right paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6646387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6646387/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 98</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
