<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,511,537]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName box="[583,698,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spatulatus">
<emphasis box="[583,698,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">spatulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to the broad or spatulate, apically rounded right paramere of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
